                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220522-128-off682 t18220522-128-crimeloc685"></join>. On the 27th of April about 9 o'clock at night, the prisoners came to buy stockings. My fellow apprentice served them, and while he turned his back I saw Hartfield take a pair off the counter, and give them to Malpas, who put them in his hat. I detained them as they were going out, and went for an officer. I took them out of his hat - Hatfield escaped but was brought back; they offered to pay after I took them out of his hat.</p>
               <p>
            
